FBIS4-8812 "dreeu074_i_94003" FBIS-EEU-94-074 Daily Report 15 Apr 1994 BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA Events in Gorazde -- 15 April Events in Gorazde -- 15 April `Massive Exodus' of Muslims AU1504175794 Paris AFP in English 1744 GMT 15 Apr 94 AU1504175794 Paris AFP English BFN [Text] Zagreb, April 15 (AFP) -- Bosnian Moslems started a massive exodus from outlying districts in the Serb-besieged Moslem enclave of Gorazde on Friday [15 April] to seek shelter within the town, UNHCR spokesman Peter Kessler said. "The situation is extremely tense" said Kessler, adding that he expected the situation in the eastern enclave to deteriorate. The exodus from northern and northeastern districts started around 3:30 P.M. (1330 GMT) and was still going on at 7 P.M., Kessler added.
